  "instruction": "Classify the given text into one of these categories: against, favor, none.\n\nThis task involves classifying social media posts (particularly tweets with hashtags like #ProLifeYouth, #SemST) about abortion-related topics.\n\nClassification guidelines:\n- \"against\": Text expressing opposition to abortion (pro-life stance)\n- \"favor\": Text expressing support for abortion rights (pro-choice stance)\n- \"none\": Text that is neutral or unrelated to abortion stance\n\nImportant context:\n- Religious or biblical quotes (such as Matthew 25:40 about caring for \"the least brothers\") that emphasize the sanctity of life or caring for the vulnerable are typically associated with pro-life (anti-abortion) positions\n- Hashtags like #ProLifeYouth indicate a pro-life stance, which means the text should be classified as \"against\" (against abortion)\n- Do not confuse being \"in favor of life\" with the \"favor\" category - \"favor\" means favoring abortion rights, while pro-life positions should be classified as \"against\"\n\nPay careful attention to religious and moral arguments that emphasize protecting life, as these typically represent opposition to abortion rather than support for it."
